on concerning the Wimmera election, referred from the Court of Disputed Returns. The central issue was determining who may vote on an adjourned polling day under the Electoral Act. The petitioner argued that any elector on the roll could vote at the adjourned poll, while the respondent contended that only electors enrolled for the specific polling place or those who attended on the original polling day but were deprived of voting could vote. The dispute arose from the interpretation of sections 153 and 139 of the Electoral Act, with practical implications for election integrity and voter rights.                                                                                     Electoral Act, sections 153 and 139                                            NaN                  N/A (Trial Case)              N/A (Trial Case)                                                                                                                                                                         N/A (Trial Case)                                                                                                                                                                                     N/A (Trial Case)                                                                                                                                                                                                                            N/A (Trial Case)                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             N/A (Trial Case)         Maximilian Hirsch               Pharez Phillips                